18#include "ODUPCEWriter.h"
19#include "ODUPCEANCommon.h"
20#include "ODWriterHelper.h"
21
22#include <stdexcept>
23#include <vector>
24
25namespace ZXing {
26namespace OneD {
27
28static const int CODE_WIDTH = 3 + // start guard
29 (7 * 6) + // bars
30 6; // end guard
31
32BitMatrix
33UPCEWriter::encode(const std::wstring& contents, int width, int height) const
34{
35 auto digits = UPCEANCommon::DigitString2IntArray<8>(
36 contents, UPCEANCommon::ComputeChecksum(UPCEANCommon::ConvertUPCEtoUPCA(contents), contents.size() == 8));
37
38 int firstDigit = digits[0];
39 if (firstDigit != 0 && firstDigit != 1) {
40 throw std::invalid_argument("Number system must be 0 or 1");
41 }
42
43 int parities = UPCEANCommon::NUMSYS_AND_CHECK_DIGIT_PATTERNS[firstDigit * 10 + digits[7]];
44 std::vector<bool> result(CODE_WIDTH, false);
45 int pos = 0;
46
47 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::START_END_PATTERN, true);
48
49 for (int i = 1; i <= 6; i++) {
50 int digit = digits[i];
51 if ((parities >> (6 - i) & 1) == 1) {
52 digit += 10;
53 }
54 pos += WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::L_AND_G_PATTERNS[digit], false);
55 }
56
57 WriterHelper::AppendPattern(result, pos, UPCEANCommon::UPCE_END_PATTERN, false);
58 return WriterHelper::RenderResult(result, width, height, _sidesMargin >= 0 ? _sidesMargin : 9);
59}
